  "texts": [
    "This resulted in 352 articles, which, after being limited to countries classified as emerging economies by the OECD and World Economic Forum and removing duplications, yielded a final dataset of 264 documents for analysis.",
    "The search results were exported from the Scopus interface into CSV format to import data into various bibliometric software tools.",
    "The Scopus data was cross-verified with Web of Science using a similar search strategy, and no additional unique records were found.",
    "Still, Scopus indexing policies related to selective journal coverage can result in missing certain publications (Mongeon and Paul-Hus, 2016), a limitation inherent in using any single database.",
    "Comparing results across multiple databases provides a more comprehensive coverage as noted by reviews on data collection methods in bibliometric studies (Aria and Cuccurullo, 2017)."
  ],
